nodes.title: Output Switch Options
widgets_values:
output switch positions:
1,1 = default image (from output 1)
1,2 = enhanced image (from output 3)
2,1 = styled image (from output 2)
2,2 = styled enhanced images (from output 3)

nodes.title: Setup and Tips
widgets_values:
On first use:
- select models and VAE
- select a default LoRA in each Load LoRA node
- select an upscale model
- select an XL ControlNet model
- add an image in each of the Load Images nodes (purple nodes)
- add a default image batch in the Load Image Batch node
- select the batch_size in CR Aspect Ratio SDXL
- set the filename_prefix in Save Image to your preferred sub-folder
- save a copy to use as a template

Tips:
- Notes can be opened by clicking on the dots (green nodes)
- Each optional component can be bypassed using logic switches (red nodes)
- The default setting for all logic switches is OFF (1)
- Use Comfyroll Manager to find any missing custom nodes
- Right-click on nodes and select Pin to pin/unpin the node

nodes.title: ControlNet Models
widgets_values:
select an XL ControlNet model to match the pre-proprocessor
(1) Canny - diffusion_pytorch_model.fp16 (or renamed)
(2) OpenPose - OpenPoseXL2
(3) Zoe depth - depth-zoe-xl-v1.0-controlnet
(4) LineArt - controlnet-sd-xl-1.0-softedge-dexined

nodes.title: Preset Mappings
widgets_values:
Prompt Mixer mappings

default with no style text

pos_g = prompt_positive
pos_l = prompt_positive
pos_r = prompt_positive
neg_g = prompt_negative
neg_l = prompt_negative
neg_r = prompt_negative

default with style text

pos_g = prompt_positive
pos_l = style_positive
pos_r = prompt_positive
neg_g = prompt_negative
neg_l = style_negative
neg_r = prompt_negative

style boost 1

pos_g = style_positive
pos_l = prompt_positive
pos_r = style_positive
neg_g = style_negative
neg_l = prompt_negative
neg_r = style_negative

style boost 2

pos_g = prompt_positive + style_positive
pos_l = prompt_positive + style_positive
pos_r = prompt_positive + style_positive
neg_g = prompt_negative + style_negative
neg_l = prompt_negative + style_negative
neg_r = prompt_negative + style_negative

style text to refiner

pos_g = prompt_positive
pos_l = prompt_positive
pos_r = style_positive
neg_g = prompt_negative
neg_l = prompt_negative
neg_r = style_negative

Switch between:
